    <p>{`Two unequally-sized partitions can be problematic. Why? See the following:`}</p>
    <p><img alt="Problematic Quicksort" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/3392/1*AuOVk7USUwVhrbmejkg5sQ.jpeg" /></p>
    <p>{`Time complexity of quicksort is dependent upon what we choose to be our partition and how sorted the list already is.`}</p>
    <p>{`Average runtime for an unsorted list + partition close to median is O(n log n).`}</p>
    <p>{`Average runtime for a sorted (or near-sorted) list or a partition that is far from the median is O(n^2).`}</p>
    <p>{`Don't use quicksort for nearly sorted lists.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "heap-sort"
    }}>{`Heap Sort`}</h2>
    <p>{`However, as similar as they are, heap sort is much better than selection sort in one massive way: its performance! Heap sort is basically a super-improved version of selection sort. Yes, it does find the largest element in an unsorted collection and orders it at the back of the list — however, it does all of this work so much faster than selection sort would!`}</p>
    <p>{`There are two parts to this:`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Build Max Heap - this is done by "Heapify-ing" the array to create a max heap`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Sorting - this is done by slowly swapping and "heapify-ing" the array, then reducing the last index to keep the order while iterating.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <p>{`Things to know about heap sort:`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Heap sort transforms the array that pass to it as it sorts; unlike some sorting algorithms, it doesn’t create an entirely separate copy of the input data (it is in-place).`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Heap sort also doesn’t need external memory, and is an internal sorting algorithm.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`It runs iteratively (and is thus non-recursive)`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Compares two elements at a time when it swaps and calls the heapify function, making it a comparison sort algorithm.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "heap-sort-implementation"
